for this system to work well.

19:50.814 --> 19:53.066
So both you and I can get paid.

19:53.150 --> 19:54.318
All right.

19:54.651 --> 19:56.361
I'll take that under advisement.

20:00.115 --> 20:01.408
Although... [chuckles]

20:02.367 --> 20:07.706
...you didn't mind my methods
when I found you in Avilés' car

20:07.789 --> 20:11.293
trying not to piss yourself. [laughs]

20:12.085 --> 20:13.462
[sighs]

20:13.545 --> 20:15.631
Don't let these badges fool you.

20:17.257 --> 20:19.051
You and I are not the same.

20:19.635 --> 20:22.262
You do your fucking job, and I'll do mine.

20:25.307 --> 20:26.558
We're done here.

20:31.271 --> 20:32.856
Ah. Almost forgot.

20:34.233 --> 20:36.693
Expect a call in the next few days.

20:36.860 --> 20:39.655
-A favor for someone important.
-A favor?

20:39.988 --> 20:41.031
[Nava]
Just an errand.

20:41.657 --> 20:45.285
Something needs to get
from point A to point B.

20:45.661 --> 20:47.412
What the fuck is that supposed to mean?

20:47.996 --> 20:50.499
Best not to ask too many questions.

20:51.083 --> 20:52.918
I'll get you the details.

20:53.710 --> 20:55.504
[car engine starts]

21:07.849 --> 21:09.184
[grunts]

21:17.859 --> 21:20.279
[pop song playing]

21:26.868 --> 21:30.163
[Chapo] Come on, fuckers. You look
too fucking sad. Drink up, fucker.

21:30.247 --> 21:31.581
Come on, Rafa.

21:50.767 --> 21:53.729
[chattering]

22:00.527 --> 22:01.862
[laughing]

22:12.372 --> 22:13.290
Ladies.

22:13.790 --> 22:17.753
Another round. And could you clear
some of these empty glasses?

22:19.087 --> 22:20.172
Dance with me.

22:20.464 --> 22:24.468
Oh, that's sweet.
But I don't want you to get in trouble.

22:24.551 --> 22:26.511
It looks like you need the job.

22:26.595 --> 22:28.472
-I'm not a waiter.
-What?

22:28.555 --> 22:29.806
I'm not a fucking waiter.

22:29.890 --> 22:32.517
[laughing]

22:34.019 --> 22:36.271
I saw you on campus, right?

22:37.022 --> 22:39.232
I think he kidnapped my professor.

22:39.316 --> 22:41.777
I returned him in one piece, didn't I?

22:42.152 --> 22:43.987
And the fucker was loaded with money.

22:44.529 --> 22:45.364
How about it?

22:46.114 --> 22:47.741
I have a boyfriend.

22:48.909 --> 22:52.412
You're lying. You don't have a boyfriend.
Dance with me.

22:53.038 --> 22:55.290
Give me one reason why not,
and I'll leave you alone.

22:55.374 --> 22:58.085
Fine. I'll give you three.

22:59.711 --> 23:00.962
Your shirt.

23:01.922 --> 23:04.216
Your pants. [laughs]

23:04.299 --> 23:06.510
And your boots. [laughs]

23:06.593 --> 23:09.012
[girls laughing]

23:12.724 --> 23:15.519
But we both know you like
what's underneath.

23:20.941 --> 23:23.402
[laughing]

23:29.074 --> 23:33.537
-What happened, buddy?
-She's a spoiled brat.

23:33.620 --> 23:34.955
Let's drink, then.

24:01.690 --> 24:05.485
[in Spanish] Rodolfo didn't want me
to say anything this morning.

24:05.861 --> 24:09.948
Something about how he's been hearing me
give speeches.

24:12.868 --> 24:15.704
Then I spoke
with his beautiful bride-to-be,

24:16.329 --> 24:19.791
and she thought it was a wonderful idea.

24:20.333 --> 24:24.921
Welcome to marriage, son.

24:25.005 --> 24:26.423
[chuckling]

24:26.506 --> 24:29.384
[in Spanish] And you're bringing in
that much money every month?

24:29.468 --> 24:31.428
Every week.

24:34.014 --> 24:37.058
This "important person"
who wants a favor from you...

24:37.893 --> 24:39.060
Nava name him?

24:39.978 --> 24:41.354
No.

24:41.438 --> 24:42.772
You know who he's talking about?

24:44.608 --> 24:46.776
Not a man you want knowing your name.

24:49.404 --> 24:52.324
My organization needs Nava,
what he delivers.

24:52.407 --> 24:55.577
But he needs to understand
that we are in this together.

24:56.036 --> 24:58.914
And that he needs to be discreet.
He goes overboard.

24:59.581 --> 25:02.667
Don't know how much longer
I can keep all of them happy.

25:05.253 --> 25:08.340
Based on the numbers you describe,
you're making real money, Miguel.

25:08.507 --> 25:11.009
The cut you deliver doesn't stop with him.

25:11.092 --> 25:13.470
Nava's got lots of mouths to feed,

25:14.179 --> 25:17.015
which means you have leverage.

25:17.682 --> 25:20.685
Uh... Sounds good.

25:53.843 --> 25:54.844
I'll see you later.

25:58.306 --> 26:00.642
[in Spanish]
Here comes a thirsty man.

26:00.725 --> 26:03.395
[in English] If the cheapest gringo I know
is gonna buy me a drink,

26:03.478 --> 26:05.814
that shit is gonna cost me something,
right?

26:05.897 --> 26:07.524
[Jaime chuckles]

26:11.444 --> 26:14.447
[Jaime] What happened to all those
big-ass Cessnas we had lining that runway?

26:14.531 --> 26:17.325
U.S.-funded Cessnas. Where'd they go?

26:17.409 --> 26:20.412
Less than a third of the program's planes
are operational.

26:20.495 --> 26:23.373
The rest have been junked,
sold the spare parts. Pieces of shit.

26:23.456 --> 26:25.500
Same old, same old. [laughs]

26:25.584 --> 26:28.336
[Jaime]
But you guys still do fly, right?

26:28.420 --> 26:30.922
[mariachi music playing]

26:31.673 --> 26:33.633
This is just me asking, Fredo.

26:33.717 --> 26:35.427
Yeah, we fly sometimes.

26:35.510 --> 26:38.221
We also take pictures.
But only when they tell us to.

26:39.389 --> 26:40.473
You, um...

26:43.143 --> 26:44.185
You seen these?

26:50.900 --> 26:52.027
Yes, I've seen them.

26:52.819 --> 26:53.653
I took them.

26:54.904 --> 26:56.239
See this number right here?

26:56.531 --> 26:58.366
The Z? It's Zavala.

26:58.450 --> 26:59.451
That's my ID.

26:59.534 --> 27:01.036
[chuckles]

27:01.119 --> 27:02.537
But that was over a year ago.

27:06.458 --> 27:07.292
A year ago?

27:08.084 --> 27:09.210
Yeah, at least.

27:11.129 --> 27:12.422
That's what you're looking for?

27:14.591 --> 27:15.675
Yeah.

27:19.721 --> 27:20.722
Yeah.

27:21.890 --> 27:23.016
You want another beer?

27:24.184 --> 27:26.728
Sure, why not. You're buying.

27:27.562 --> 27:30.482
-[in Spanish] Señor! Two more!
-Three!

28:55.358 --> 28:57.152
[car engine starts]

31:04.946 --> 31:08.074
[chatter in Spanish]

31:27.427 --> 31:31.097
[Chilo Escobedo's "Dame Amor" playing]

31:50.199 --> 31:51.326
[in Spanish]
I'll have a beer.

32:08.051 --> 32:10.678
[mariachi music playing]

32:23.149 --> 32:24.150
Take one.

32:26.319 --> 32:28.071
Or else I'll finish the whole pack.

32:52.512 --> 32:55.223
[man on TV in English] How do I know
you're not a chivato, too, Tony?

32:55.890 --> 32:57.183
Hey, Sosa.

32:59.519 --> 33:00.353
[in Spanish] Waiter?

33:00.436 --> 33:02.146
[in English]
Let's get this straight, now.

33:02.230 --> 33:03.856
[in Spanish]
Are you fucking serious?

33:04.065 --> 33:05.233
A waiter.

33:05.316 --> 33:08.152
[in English] I never fucked anybody over
who didn't have it coming.

33:08.236 --> 33:13.074
[in Spanish] I could buy
that fucking nightclub. Stupid brat.

33:13.574 --> 33:17.620
[in English] ...and my word and I don't
break them for no one. You understand?

33:19.580 --> 33:23.668
That piece of shit up there,
I never liked him, I never trusted him.

33:23.751 --> 33:27.630
For all I know, he had me set up
and had my friend Angel Fernandez killed.

33:28.339 --> 33:30.758
But that's history. I'm here, he's not.

33:30.842 --> 33:35.805
You want to go on with me, say it.
You don't, then you make a move.

33:36.764 --> 33:37.932
[chuckles]

33:40.476 --> 33:43.855
[Kiki in Spanish]
And they put me on a bus, shipped me home.

33:43.938 --> 33:45.273
[exhales]

33:46.357 --> 33:49.527
Didn't even get to say goodbye to my wife.

33:50.486 --> 33:51.696
And she's pregnant.

33:51.779 --> 33:53.614
[ranchera music playing]

33:57.618 --> 33:58.828
Where did you say you are from?

33:59.370 --> 34:00.455
Michoacán.

34:01.706 --> 34:03.207
Doesn't sound like it.

34:03.291 --> 34:05.168
[in accented English]
Speak English too long.

34:06.294 --> 34:07.170
[Kiki laughs]

34:08.337 --> 34:10.965
[in Spanish]
Hey, any work around here?

34:11.591 --> 34:12.925
I'm a hard worker.

34:14.302 --> 34:17.513
Just need enough money to get north again.

34:20.600 --> 34:21.642
No.

34:23.061 --> 34:24.771
I don't know about any work.

34:27.732 --> 34:28.733
Go ahead.

34:29.609 --> 34:31.277
-You sure?
-Yes.

34:47.001 --> 34:49.170
[phone rings]

34:52.298 --> 34:54.092
-[in English] Hello?
-Oh, hey, babe.

34:54.467 --> 34:55.343
Hey.

34:55.718 --> 34:58.805
Hey, so I won't be able
to make it home tonight.

34:58.888 --> 34:59.722
Are you okay?

34:59.806 --> 35:01.682
No, I'm fine. I'm just on a job.

35:02.934 --> 35:05.645
-Okay. Be careful.
-I will be.

35:06.229 --> 35:08.189
-I love you.
-Love you too.

35:08.272 --> 35:09.315
Okay, bye.

35:22.495 --> 35:24.163
[vehicle approaching]

35:24.789 --> 35:25.832
[tires skid]

35:31.295 --> 35:32.672
[engine stops]

35:34.090 --> 35:35.424
[door opens]

35:44.475 --> 35:45.977
[indistinct chatter]

35:46.686 --> 35:48.437
[rooster cocking]

36:14.547 --> 36:16.632
[man in Spanish]
Heads up. The buses are coming.

36:41.240 --> 36:43.910
All right, everyone.
Start forming a line over here.

36:44.202 --> 36:45.161
Quickly.

36:48.164 --> 36:49.332
Move it.

36:57.924 --> 36:59.508
Speed it up.

37:10.686 --> 37:13.356
Hold up. I don't know you.

37:14.065 --> 37:15.399
[man]
I know him.

37:17.276 --> 37:19.028
He's my nephew from Michoacán.

37:20.613 --> 37:22.156
Had trouble up north, but...

37:22.990 --> 37:24.283
he's a hard worker.

37:27.411 --> 37:28.579
From Michoacán.

37:35.044 --> 37:36.921
Okay, get on the bus.

37:38.881 --> 37:40.466
Go!

37:50.893 --> 37:51.894
[whispers] Thanks.

37:52.353 --> 37:54.063
You owe me half your pay.

37:55.356 --> 37:57.316
Every day you work.

38:00.486 --> 38:01.821
Put the bag on.

38:02.405 --> 38:04.323
Don't take it off until they tell you to.

38:07.159 --> 38:08.411
[man]
All right, fuckers.

38:08.828 --> 38:10.204
Time to get to work.

38:26.053 --> 38:27.179
[man]
Take them off!

38:27.596 --> 38:29.432
Take off your hoods.

38:31.851 --> 38:34.061
Let's go. Get off the bus.

38:39.692 --> 38:41.027
Hurry up.

39:03.007 --> 39:04.133
[man] Come on!

39:05.051 --> 39:06.177
Time to work!

39:07.762 --> 39:10.639
They'll give you your tools.
You know what to do.

39:10.723 --> 39:12.433
Hurry up, we don't have much time.

39:37.416 --> 39:40.002
Our crew works one of the northern fields.

39:41.295 --> 39:42.963
Ever pick weed before?

39:45.257 --> 39:46.926
I'll show you what to do. Follow me.

40:09.532 --> 40:12.868
[Sears in English] The Mazatlán office
must have a real hard-on for this asshole.

40:14.036 --> 40:16.122
[Knapp] Cochiloco.

40:16.914 --> 40:17.748
"Crazy Pig."

40:17.832 --> 40:20.042
Damn, that's a good fucking nickname.

40:20.501 --> 40:23.379
[Sears]
Disco, whorehouse, barbershop.

40:24.171 --> 40:26.048
Guy's hitting the dirt-bag trifecta.

40:26.715 --> 40:28.217
You think he likes it?

40:28.884 --> 40:31.554
I mean, when they gave it to him,
you think he was like,

40:31.971 --> 40:34.723
"Cool. Cochiloco. That's me."

40:39.270 --> 40:40.438
[phone rings]

40:42.731 --> 40:43.566
[in English] Hello.

40:43.649 --> 40:47.319
-Jaime. Ed Heath.
-Thanks for getting back to me, Ed.

40:47.403 --> 40:52.575
Well, uh, a couple of months ago,
we, uh... we asked the eradication guys

40:52.658 --> 40:55.703
to do a fly-over in the desert
outside of Guadalajara.

40:55.786 --> 40:58.789
And we finally got the pictures back.

40:59.165 --> 40:59.999
Uh-huh.

41:01.709 --> 41:03.043
They're at least a year old.

41:04.378 --> 41:07.798
And no flights have been ordered
over that area since that time.

41:08.757 --> 41:12.344
-So what are you saying?
-The eradication program's bullshit.

41:12.428 --> 41:16.140
I mean, it's a fraud,
or at least it's been compromised.

41:19.935 --> 41:21.645
The thing is, Jaime... [ sighs]

41:21.729 --> 41:24.315
...that's a bit of a complicated knot
you're tugging on there.

41:25.774 --> 41:26.901
I don't understand.

41:26.984 --> 41:32.823
Well, as far as the Mexican government
is concerned, the program works fine.

41:32.907 --> 41:36.577
-I think that's the problem--
-And the State Department agrees.

41:37.161 --> 41:38.704
It's considered a model program.

41:40.122 --> 41:43.709
They see it as "strong evidence
of the successful partnership

41:43.792 --> 41:45.753
between our two governments."

41:46.337 --> 41:47.755
That's a direct quote from State.

41:49.006 --> 41:50.090
I see.

41:52.551 --> 41:56.055
Jaime, we're guests down here.

41:56.805 --> 42:01.602
And people don't like it when guests
start nosing through the cupboards.

42:01.685 --> 42:04.021
You understand
where I'm pointing at with this one?

42:04.104 --> 42:06.607
Yeah, I do. I do. That...

42:08.150 --> 42:10.069
That all tracks on this end.

42:11.737 --> 42:14.073
Good. [sighs] Good.

42:14.865 --> 42:18.285
Look, I don't like it any more than you,

42:18.369 --> 42:21.539
but this is the deal.

42:21.622 --> 42:23.958
Yes, sir.
I appreciate you taking the time.

42:44.478 --> 42:46.146
[in Spanish]
Your hands will get used to it.

42:52.611 --> 42:53.696
[sighs]

42:54.238 --> 42:55.864
How big is this place?

42:59.243 --> 43:00.619
I've never seen the end of it.

43:32.943 --> 43:34.111
You should eat.

43:34.820 --> 43:37.781
It's all we get for the rest of the day.

43:43.621 --> 43:45.331
-[El Azul] Cuco.
-[Cuco] What's up, boss?

43:50.419 --> 43:51.545
[El Azul]
Where is Rafa?

43:52.421 --> 43:53.922
[Cuco]
He had an emergency in the city.

43:55.090 --> 43:57.676
[El Azul] We came out here
and that motherfucker's in the city?

43:59.219 --> 44:02.681
-[Tomás] Just ask for the inventory.
-[El Azul] Show me the inventory.

44:02.765 --> 44:05.392
Pepe!
Bring the inventory list and two beers.

44:06.268 --> 44:09.063
Make sure they're cold. It's fucking hot.

44:15.986 --> 44:17.571
[bell rings]

44:17.655 --> 44:20.282
[man]
Back to work, fuckers.

44:20.366 --> 44:22.576
[chattering]

44:25.412 --> 44:27.247
[dialing rotary phone]

44:33.629 --> 44:35.214
[in Spanish] It's me.

44:36.757 --> 44:40.052
Listen-- Listen to me!

44:41.178 --> 44:42.846
You want payback, right?

44:44.348 --> 44:47.810
Come to my hotel tonight.

44:50.688 --> 44:53.649
Tell them you're my personal guest.
And dress nice.

44:54.441 --> 44:55.609
I'm serious.

44:55.693 --> 44:56.819
Okay, then.

45:14.378 --> 45:15.838
[Félix]
I have a job for you.

45:17.256 --> 45:19.299
Get some men.

45:38.277 --> 45:40.612
[bell rings]

45:41.196 --> 45:42.865
[man in Spanish]
Time to go. Move it.

45:44.283 --> 45:45.284
That's it.

45:49.580 --> 45:51.790
Michoacán. Back to the bus.

46:01.341 --> 46:03.302
Look at these poor fuckers.

46:03.969 --> 46:06.388
Working under the sun all fucking day.

46:24.573 --> 46:25.949
Hold on.

46:26.366 --> 46:27.868
Wait for me right here.

46:39.671 --> 46:40.964
[Tomás]
Where are you going, boss?

46:47.846 --> 46:48.680
[man] Let's go.

46:52.267 --> 46:53.519
Let's go.

47:03.237 --> 47:04.446
[man] Hoods on.

47:23.173 --> 47:24.466
[Tomás] Boss!

47:25.384 --> 47:27.636
Rafa is on the phone!

47:28.262 --> 47:29.221
Be right there.

47:35.227 --> 47:37.312
[bus engine starts]

47:40.566 --> 47:41.483
[sighs]

47:41.567 --> 47:43.318
[in English]
What is this asshole up to now?

47:47.781 --> 47:48.949
What the fuck?

47:51.368 --> 47:52.619
[Sears] Jesus.

48:11.346 --> 48:13.056
[in Spanish]
You look very handsome, my love.

48:13.724 --> 48:15.309
You look good, too.

48:16.935 --> 48:18.103
Are you ready?

48:23.734 --> 48:25.152
[man]
Ladies and gentlemen,

48:25.235 --> 48:31.199
Mr. and Mrs. Rodolfo Celis invite you
to join them on the dance floor!

48:31.700 --> 48:33.201
[band music playing]

48:42.502 --> 48:44.755
[chattering]

49:03.857 --> 49:05.901
[Sears in English]
What the fuck is this guy doing?

49:06.693 --> 49:09.571
What kind of party
did shit-bird make the cut on?

49:12.574 --> 49:15.202
Hope you got
your dancing shoes, there, Butch.

49:16.620 --> 49:18.956
-Find a place to park.
-Yup.

49:41.353 --> 49:43.647
[chattering]

49:48.402 --> 49:49.778
Ah!

49:50.612 --> 49:51.822
[in Spanish] Sit down.

50:28.191 --> 50:29.901
[speaking indistinctly]

50:55.218 --> 50:56.970
[in Spanish]
See you tomorrow, Michoacán.

51:18.241 --> 51:20.827
[phone rings]

51:23.622 --> 51:26.541
-[in English] DEA.
-Hey, it's Kiki. Where's Kuykendall?

51:26.625 --> 51:28.627
Kiki, where've you been?
We've been looking for you.

51:28.710 --> 51:30.712
Mika's in labor. She's at the hospital.

51:32.214 --> 51:34.174
[band music playing]

51:36.426 --> 51:38.970
[laughing]

51:39.054 --> 51:41.014
[in Spanish]
My queen was thirsty.

51:41.515 --> 51:42.516
Always.

51:43.100 --> 51:45.685
-How about we have another drink?
-You want another one?

51:52.818 --> 51:53.860
Excuse me.

51:59.783 --> 52:00.867
Excuse me.

52:01.618 --> 52:02.828
What's up?

52:02.911 --> 52:04.579
We gonna have a problem?

52:15.006 --> 52:17.300
I have to go get a martini, my friend.

52:24.933 --> 52:27.435
-What's wrong with your brother?
-[Benjamín] He's pissed.

52:49.207 --> 52:51.251
Ladies and gentlemen,
thanks for being here.

52:51.334 --> 52:53.712
I would like to ask you
to go downstairs to your tables.

52:53.795 --> 52:56.131
The party is better down there.

52:57.048 --> 52:58.133
Thank you.

53:03.555 --> 53:06.725
I didn't know
they allowed assholes at the party.

53:06.808 --> 53:08.351
Hey, put that down!

53:08.435 --> 53:11.897
Hey, Ramon! Don't do something stupid.

53:12.355 --> 53:15.108
I brought you here to listen, not talk.

53:15.192 --> 53:16.902
Tie up your mutts.

53:16.985 --> 53:18.403
That goes for all of you.

53:22.324 --> 53:23.450
Let's see, Mr. Nava.

53:25.535 --> 53:29.122
You received some cash today.

53:29.206 --> 53:33.501
For the second time,
the envelope was light. Right?

53:35.670 --> 53:39.883
And in response,
you decided to make another point.

53:41.218 --> 53:42.886
Something to teach them a lesson.

53:44.512 --> 53:47.766
Show what happens to men who disobey you.

53:49.893 --> 53:51.144
Check all the rooms.

54:02.239 --> 54:03.865
Search the property.

54:04.199 --> 54:05.367
[Félix]
Thing is, Comandante...

54:07.494 --> 54:08.328
so did I.

54:11.998 --> 54:13.416
Good evening.

54:15.001 --> 54:17.462
Your weapons, gentlemen.

54:17.587 --> 54:21.549
Fucking chinolo. You set me up.

54:23.051 --> 54:25.136
The brothers want blood.

54:25.804 --> 54:27.347
And that's fair.

54:27.889 --> 54:30.600
So you'll get the man responsible
for your cousin's death.

54:30.934 --> 54:33.353
[grunting]

54:44.614 --> 54:47.659
[Nava] What makes you so sure
I'll accept these terms?

54:47.742 --> 54:50.078
[scoffs] You have to understand something.

54:50.161 --> 54:52.372
We are the ones that grow it.

54:52.872 --> 54:57.168
You make sure nobody fucks with it.
That's it.

54:59.462 --> 55:01.131
And I run the show.

55:02.257 --> 55:04.551
Without me, you got nothing.

55:05.135 --> 55:07.262
But if you want,
we can throw away everything.

55:07.637 --> 55:10.682
And then you can explain to all the men
on your payroll why their money is gone.

55:12.309 --> 55:15.979
As long as the money is coming in,
Don Miguel.

55:17.647 --> 55:19.733
But the minute it's not,

55:20.108 --> 55:23.570
I'll be the one
putting a bullet in your face.

55:29.451 --> 55:34.456
I want you to go back downstairs
and sit at that table,

55:34.539 --> 55:36.541
so that everyone sees
you having a drink together.

55:36.624 --> 55:38.001
Because this is over.

55:39.419 --> 55:41.129
It's over. Understood?

55:47.135 --> 55:48.511
One more thing.

55:48.887 --> 55:53.600
You can tell this "someone important"
I'm not in the business of doing favors.

55:56.061 --> 55:58.980
Now we are done here.

56:02.317 --> 56:05.528
What's up, Ramon?
I told you to dress nice, fucker.

56:05.612 --> 56:06.863
This is nice.

56:09.282 --> 56:10.825
Ramon.

56:12.077 --> 56:13.661
[Félix]
Never forget where you come from.

56:15.372 --> 56:18.291
We Sinaloans may scatter to the winds,

56:18.375 --> 56:25.131
but our roots
keep us planted firmly on the ground.

56:27.175 --> 56:31.012
Know that today,
you have taken part in a sacred act.

56:32.555 --> 56:35.392
"The blood of the covenant
is thicker than the water of the womb."

56:35.517 --> 56:39.854
There is no stronger bond
than that of the family you choose.

56:40.605 --> 56:45.318
And today, you decided to be together,
to be a family.

56:46.444 --> 56:47.529
You're screwed.

56:47.612 --> 56:48.905
[all chuckle]

56:48.988 --> 56:53.243
So, cheers,
and long live the bride and groom.

56:53.326 --> 56:55.954
[cheering and applause]

57:09.759 --> 57:11.719
[Celis]
One more thing, if I may.

57:11.803 --> 57:17.475
What politician can resist a microphone?

57:17.559 --> 57:19.269
[all chuckle]

57:22.063 --> 57:27.777
As father of the groom, I'd like
to take a moment to thank our host.

57:28.278 --> 57:29.988
When I first met Miguel Ángel,

57:30.280 --> 57:32.740
all he had to his name
was a pistol and a badge

57:32.824 --> 57:36.536
and someone had to loan him
the money for the gun.

57:36.619 --> 57:38.037
[Celis chuckles]

57:38.955 --> 57:42.208
As Rodolfo's friend,

57:43.001 --> 57:47.547
this man loved and protected my son

57:48.798 --> 57:50.633
like his own.

57:52.260 --> 57:54.762
For that, I have always been grateful.

57:56.598 --> 57:59.601
Now, standing here tonight
in his beautiful hotel,

58:00.852 --> 58:03.771
seeing the man he's become,

58:04.564 --> 58:06.274
and the success he's achieved...

58:07.734 --> 58:09.611
I'm also proud. Beyond measure.

58:11.988 --> 58:13.656
Let's raise a glass.

58:14.449 --> 58:19.412
To my old friend,
one of Guadalajara's rising stars,

58:19.496 --> 58:21.873
Miguel Ángel Félix Gallardo.

58:23.124 --> 58:24.083
For my godfather!

58:24.167 --> 58:27.879
[cheering and applause]

58:39.599 --> 58:41.976
[in Spanish]
Kiki, she's in labor.

58:42.060 --> 58:44.771
-Where is she?
-In the operating room. This way.

58:49.025 --> 58:50.443
Hey, you can't be in here.

58:50.527 --> 58:53.112
-It's okay. He's my husband.
-[in English] Hey, baby.

58:53.196 --> 58:55.406
[nurse in Spanish] He has to clean
and wash, please.

58:55.490 --> 58:57.825
-[chuckles]
-[in English] You look beautiful.

58:58.326 --> 59:00.119
I love you, baby. I love you.

59:00.203 --> 59:02.705
[band music playing]

59:17.887 --> 59:18.930
[in Spanish] Dance?

59:21.516 --> 59:23.476
Don't look at her. I'm talking to you.

59:23.977 --> 59:26.563
Sorry, man. I just beat you to it.
Shall we?

1:00:26.998 --> 1:00:28.750
[mariachi music playing]

1:00:58.780 --> 1:01:01.658
[chattering]

1:01:07.538 --> 1:01:10.249
[singing in Spanish]

1:01:19.676 --> 1:01:21.719
Looks like your problems got resolved.

1:01:24.263 --> 1:01:26.849
Took a friend's advice.

1:01:28.810 --> 1:01:32.522
Thank you, sir. For everything.

1:01:35.692 --> 1:01:37.318
[cheering]

1:01:46.869 --> 1:01:49.414
$100,000 for the other governors.

1:01:49.497 --> 1:01:51.499
$200,000 for me.

1:01:52.583 --> 1:01:54.293
My advice isn't free.

1:01:54.794 --> 1:01:56.587
Neither is my friendship.

1:01:58.673 --> 1:02:02.385
Have the money delivered
to our rooms tonight.

1:02:04.595 --> 1:02:05.805
What did you think?

1:02:06.973 --> 1:02:10.560
Just because you bought a hotel, a few
banks, doesn't change how things work.

1:02:11.018 --> 1:02:13.563
Or who you are under that suit.

1:02:15.523 --> 1:02:18.151
Don't forget who you really are.

1:02:21.612 --> 1:02:23.364
This is how business is done...

1:02:24.824 --> 1:02:25.783
my son.

1:02:33.624 --> 1:02:34.584
[grunts]

1:02:37.003 --> 1:02:39.547
This motherfucker needs to see my face.

1:02:50.558 --> 1:02:51.809
[groans]

1:02:56.022 --> 1:02:58.399
[grunts]

1:03:06.699 --> 1:03:08.618
[groaning]

1:03:12.288 --> 1:03:15.082
[in Spanish] I called Maria
so she could take care of Kikito.

1:03:15.166 --> 1:03:16.292
And Antonio brought me.

1:03:16.959 --> 1:03:20.755
She wanted to drive herself here,
but I didn't let her.

1:03:20.838 --> 1:03:22.089
[whispers] He came early.

1:03:23.925 --> 1:03:26.177
He wasn't supposed to be born yet.

1:03:27.845 --> 1:03:29.096
[in English] I'm sorry.

1:03:29.472 --> 1:03:32.850
It's okay. You're here.

1:03:36.646 --> 1:03:37.814
[Mika chuckles]

1:03:37.897 --> 1:03:38.773
[clears throat]

1:03:38.856 --> 1:03:41.526
[in Spanish]
I'm going to call Maria. I'll be back.

1:03:41.609 --> 1:03:42.777
Thank you.

1:03:52.078 --> 1:03:53.246
[in English] Look at my boy.

1:03:53.746 --> 1:03:55.623
He came out when he wanted to.

1:03:56.290 --> 1:03:58.960
Stubborn. Like his dad.

1:04:02.421 --> 1:04:05.007
Work didn't know where you were.
You want to check in with them?

1:04:05.091 --> 1:04:06.217
Mm-mmm.

1:04:07.552 --> 1:04:09.554
Nah, I just want to sit here a while.

1:04:11.347 --> 1:04:12.849
With my baby boy.

1:04:21.107 --> 1:04:23.150
[church bells ringing]

1:04:25.653 --> 1:04:28.823
-[Kiki in English] Hey, Suzy. Is he in?
-Yeah. Congratulations, Kiki.

1:04:28.906 --> 1:04:29.866
Oh, thank you.

1:04:40.042 --> 1:04:40.877
[Kiki] Sir.

1:04:45.047 --> 1:04:48.551
I picked this myself,
200 miles north of the city.

1:04:51.596 --> 1:04:54.056
The eradication program is bullshit.

1:04:57.059 --> 1:04:57.977
Brass know that?

1:04:58.060 --> 1:05:01.230
[chuckles] Christ.
I don't know what they know.

1:05:01.314 --> 1:05:03.608
-You can see it from outer space.
-I believe you.

1:05:03.691 --> 1:05:06.652
But if you ever do something as stupid
as going up there alone again,

1:05:06.736 --> 1:05:08.821
you can pack your shit,
'cause I'm sending you home.

1:05:09.864 --> 1:05:10.823
Yes, sir.

1:05:13.034 --> 1:05:14.785
-Desert dope?
-[Kiki] Yep.

1:05:15.661 --> 1:05:16.621
I tried to tell you.

1:05:16.704 --> 1:05:21.250
Everyone's involved. The DFS.
Jalisco P.D. Everyone.

1:05:21.334 --> 1:05:23.753
[Jaime] You add whoever's running
the eradication program,

1:05:23.836 --> 1:05:25.546
we got ourselves a conspiracy.

1:05:26.088 --> 1:05:30.217
Well, that conspiracy threw itself
one hell of a party last night.

1:05:30.635 --> 1:05:32.887
I bought these off
the wedding photographer.

1:05:32.970 --> 1:05:34.221
We got ourselves...

1:05:35.389 --> 1:05:38.392
governors, senators,

1:05:38.476 --> 1:05:41.354
brand-name big shots
like the head of the DFS...

1:05:42.188 --> 1:05:45.900
and a who's who of Sinaloan dirt-bags.

1:05:45.983 --> 1:05:47.944
I've never seen so many assholes
under one roof.

1:05:48.027 --> 1:05:49.904
Someone is making them all sing in tune.

1:05:49.987 --> 1:05:51.489
Running dope like it's a corporation.

1:05:51.572 --> 1:05:54.075
All right, well,
who's our Lee Iacocca then?

1:06:01.791 --> 1:06:04.877
Who's that guy?
The skinny dude getting his ass kissed?

1:06:06.003 --> 1:06:06.879
[Knapp] Sinaloan.

1:06:06.963 --> 1:06:09.632
Owned the hotel, plus a bunch
of other shit in the town,

1:06:09.715 --> 1:06:12.385
and he was definitely
the El Padrino at this thing.

1:06:12.468 --> 1:06:13.803
[Jaime] The Godfather.

1:06:16.555 --> 1:06:19.141
-[Kiki] What's his name?
-[Knapp] Miguel Félix Gallardo.

1:06:24.647 --> 1:06:25.481
[Kiki] That's him.

1:06:26.148 --> 1:06:27.233
That's our guy.
